1. Grozna sam se probudila danas. (*grozna* - adjective in feminine form, nominative case) (I woke up feeling terrible today.)

2. Njena odjeća izgleda grozno. (*grozno* - adverb) (Her clothes look terrible.)

3. Ovo jelo ima grozan miris. (*grozan* - adjective in masculine form, accusative case) (This dish has a terrible smell.)

4. Tvoje ponašanje je bilo grozno. (*grozno* - adverb) (Your behavior was terrible.)

5. Osjećam se grozno nakon jučerašnje žurke. (*grozno* - adverb) (I feel terrible after yesterday's party.)

6. Groznu istinu je teško prihvatiti. (*groznu* - adjective in feminine form, accusative case) (It's hard to accept the terrible truth.)

7. Čim je progovorio, znao sam da će biti grozno. (*grozno* - adverb) (As soon as he spoke, I knew it was going to be terrible.)

8. Ona je jedna grozna osoba. (*grozna* - adjective in feminine form, nominative case) (She's a terrible person.)

9. Grozan zvuk me probudio. (*grozan* - adjective in masculine form, nominative case) (A terrible sound woke me up.)

10. Njegov izgled je bio grozan nakon nesreće. (*grozan* - adjective in masculine form, nominative case) (His appearance was terrible after the accident.)